Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{½%can} in a #sieve{}.

Trim the @aubergine{1}(trimmed and halved lengthways) into long strips, then chopped
widthways into thirds.

Pop the aubergine onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the
@North Indian style spice mix{1}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to
coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @desiccated coconut{15%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until
lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Watch it like a hawk as it can burn easily.

Once toasted, transfer to a #small bowl{} and set aside.

Pour the @water{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{¼%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once
boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

Pop your (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the @rogan josh curry paste{50%g} and fry for ~{1%minute} more, then
stir in the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}, @vegetable stock
paste{10%g}, @sugar{½%tsp} and @water{100%ml}.

Stir through the chickpeas, then simmer until the sauce has thickened,
~{10-15%minutes}.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the
toasted coconut.

Stir the roasted aubergine, @mango chutney{40%g} and @butter{20%g} through the
curry, then taste and add salt and pepper if needed.

Spoon the rice and aubergine curry into your #bowls{} and top with a dollop of
@yoghurt{75%g} to finish.

Enjoy!